data.text:
Tricia Tanaka Is Dead

Hurley's discovery of an old, wrecked car on the island leads him on a mission of hope not only for himself, but for a fellow survivor in need of some faith. Meanwhile, Kate and Sawyer reunite with their fellow castaways, but Kate is still torn about leaving Jack behind with "The Others."

Chapter Thirteen

A medical issue may cause Jane to miss her graduation. Alba has a problem but is too embarrassed to talk about it, and Michael thinks he has finally identified Sin Rostro.

The Lie

Time shifts on the Island throw Sawyer, Juliet, Faraday, Locke and everyone else for a loop; Ben enlists Jack to get the Oceanic Six back together; Hurley enlists his parents' help when Sayid is tranquilized.
